article.headline: Cent. Michigan 91, Ohio 85
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. -- Trey Zeigler scored 24 points to help Central Michigan snap a three-game losing streak with a 91-85 victory over Ohio on Wednesday night. Zeigler led five players in double digits for the Chippewas (6-15, 3-5 Mid-American), who led the entire second half and by as many as 14 points. Jalin Thomas added 22 points for Central Michigan while Derek Jackson scored 14, Finis Craddock 12 and Colin Voss 10. The Chippewas shot 50 percent from the field and took the rebounding advantage 34-29. D.J. Cooper scored a game-high 30 points for the Bobcats (10-12, 3-5), who shot 51.9 percent from the field. Tommy Freeman added 16 points for Ohio while Ricardo Johnson scored 11 and DeVaughn Washington 10. Ohio's Reggie Keely pulled down a game-high 10 rebounds.
